headline: Investors Expect a ‘Hawkish Cut’
summary: Investors are pretty much convinced that the Federal Reserve will cut interest rates on Wednesday, but they’ve been increasingly expecting a “hawkish cut.”  Interest-rate futures showed Tuesday morning that traders see a 32% chance that the Fed cuts rates at least three times in 2026, according to CME Group, down from 56% shortly before Thanksgiving.  Last month, signs that the Fed would cut rates at its upcoming meeting initially caused traders to also start expecting more cuts next year.

headline: Will SEC Approval of New Treasury Clearing House Change CME Group's (CME) Risk‑Resilience Narrative?
summary: CME Group recently received SEC approval for its new securities clearing house, CME Securities Clearing Inc., expected to launch in the second quarter of 2026 to support compliance with upcoming U.S. Treasury and repo clearing mandates. This regulatory green light, coming shortly after CME’s efforts to reinforce systems following an hours-long data center outage, underscores how the company is balancing growth in critical market plumbing with tighter expectations on operational...
